wfVinesBaseDelete.name: wfVinesBaseDelete
wfVinesBaseDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. This value determines whether or not VINES is configured on this slot.

wfVinesBaseDisable.name: wfVinesBaseDisable
wfVinesBaseDisable.description: This parameter determines whether or not VINES is to startup.

wfVinesBaseState.name: wfVinesBaseState
wfVinesBaseState.description: This parameter reflects the current state of VINES.

wfVinesBaseUserNetid.name: wfVinesBaseUserNetid
wfVinesBaseUserNetid.description: The network ID as defined by the user. A null value indicates that the user is not configuring a Network ID and that the the router should assign it.

wfVinesBaseRouterNetid.name: wfVinesBaseRouterNetid
wfVinesBaseRouterNetid.description: The network ID as defined by the router. If the user configures a Network ID in the above attribute, we will take that value and add in the Wellfleet code for VINES and save it here.

wfVinesBaseBcastClass.name: wfVinesBaseBcastClass
wfVinesBaseBcastClass.description: The broadcast modifier. This value defines the class of broadcast packets that are originated by this node.

wfVinesBaseNetworkSize.name: wfVinesBaseNetworkSize
wfVinesBaseNetworkSize.description: Allows the network administrator to pre-configure the size of the network. The default is 0.

wfVinesBaseHostSize.name: wfVinesBaseHostSize
wfVinesBaseHostSize.description: Allows the network administrator to pre-configure the expected number of neighbor. The dafault is 0.

wfVinesBaseRtpMode.name: wfVinesBaseRtpMode
wfVinesBaseRtpMode.description: This parameter will determine whether sequenced RTP or Non Sequenced RTP will be supported or both modes will be available.

wfVinesBaseLogFilter.name: wfVinesBaseLogFilter
wfVinesBaseLogFilter.description: Filter out some log messages, Default filters out trace messages. ??? Change this later to FILTER_TRACE ???

wfVinesBaseRouterSeqNumber.name: wfVinesBaseRouterSeqNumber
wfVinesBaseRouterSeqNumber.description: This parameter keeps track of the of current router sequence number

wfVinesBaseSoloSlotMask.name: wfVinesBaseSoloSlotMask
wfVinesBaseSoloSlotMask.description: Slot mask for which slots VINES soloist is eligible to run on. The MSBit represents slot 1, the next most significant bit represents slot 2, and so on... Slots can be 1-14. Default is all slots on a BCN.

wfVinesBaseSoloistSlot.name: wfVinesBaseSoloistSlot
wfVinesBaseSoloistSlot.description: Tells which slot the VINES soloist is running on

wfVinesIpTotIn.name: wfVinesIpTotIn
wfVinesIpTotIn.description: The total number of VINES IP packets received.

wfVinesIpTotOut.name: wfVinesIpTotOut
wfVinesIpTotOut.description: The total number of VINES IP packets sent.

wfVinesIpBad.name: wfVinesIpBad
wfVinesIpBad.description: The total number of badly formed packets that were received. This field is incremented when a packet is received with an improper checksum.

wfVinesIpRouted.name: wfVinesIpRouted
wfVinesIpRouted.description: The total number of packets received that were routed to another node. This statistic includes the number of IP packets encapsulated within routed VINES IP headers. Each routed packet counts as both an incoming and outgoing packet.

wfVinesIpRoutedHWM.name: wfVinesIpRoutedHWM
wfVinesIpRoutedHWM.description: The largest number of packets routed in one second since the server was last booted.

wfVinesIpBcast.name: wfVinesIpBcast
wfVinesIpBcast.description: The number of VINES IP broadcast packets sent, both locally generated and routed from other nodes.

wfVinesIpBcastHWM.name: wfVinesIpBcastHWM
wfVinesIpBcastHWM.description: The largest number of packets broadcast in one second since the server was last booted.

wfVinesIpReass.name: wfVinesIpReass
wfVinesIpReass.description: The number of times that packets were reassembled. Reassemblies result from the transmission of packets that must be broken into smaller pieces, then reassembled due to differences in transmission media.

wfVinesIpFrags.name: wfVinesIpFrags
wfVinesIpFrags.description: The number of packet fragmentations performed.

wfVinesIpToDodIP.name: wfVinesIpToDodIP
wfVinesIpToDodIP.description: The number of packets that VINES IP passed to IP for encapsulation in IP headers. These packets were initially handled by VINES IP, but were passed to IP for routing. If the TCP/IP Server-to-Server option is not installed, this value will be zero.

wfVinesIpFromDodIP.name: wfVinesIpFromDodIP
wfVinesIpFromDodIP.description: The number of packets that VINES IP received from IP to be decapsulated into VINES packets. IP initially handled these packets, but had to pass them on to VINES IP for routing. If the server is not running a TCP/IP option, this value will be zero.

wfVinesRtpNbrNumber.name: wfVinesRtpNbrNumber
wfVinesRtpNbrNumber.description: Number of entries in the Table of Neighbors.

wfVinesRtpNbrTable.name: wfVinesRtpNbrTable
wfVinesRtpNbrTable.description: This is the Table of Neighbors.

wfVinesRtpNbrEntry.name: wfVinesRtpNbrEntry
wfVinesRtpNbrEntry.description: An entry in the Table of Neighbors.

wfVinesRtpNbrNetId.name: wfVinesRtpNbrNetId
wfVinesRtpNbrNetId.description: The network ID of this neighbor.

wfVinesRtpNbrSubNetId.name: wfVinesRtpNbrSubNetId
wfVinesRtpNbrSubNetId.description: The subnetwork ID of this neighbor.

wfVinesRtpNbrType.name: wfVinesRtpNbrType
wfVinesRtpNbrType.description: The type of node: client or server.

wfVinesRtpNbrIfType.name: wfVinesRtpNbrIfType
wfVinesRtpNbrIfType.description: This describes the type of interface.

wfVinesRtpNbrRtType.name: wfVinesRtpNbrRtType
wfVinesRtpNbrRtType.description: The route type of this nbr

wfVinesRtpNbrNumPaths.name: wfVinesRtpNbrNumPaths
wfVinesRtpNbrNumPaths.description: The number of paths to the Nbr

wfVinesRtpRtNumber.name: wfVinesRtpRtNumber
wfVinesRtpRtNumber.description: Number of entries in the Table of Networks.

wfVinesRtpRtTable.name: wfVinesRtpRtTable
wfVinesRtpRtTable.description: This is the Table of Networks.

wfVinesRtpRtEntry.name: wfVinesRtpRtEntry
wfVinesRtpRtEntry.description: An entry in the Table of Networks.

wfVinesRtpRtMetric.name: wfVinesRtpRtMetric
wfVinesRtpRtMetric.description: The routing metric to get to this network.

wfVinesRtpRtIdle.name: wfVinesRtpRtIdle
wfVinesRtpRtIdle.description: The idle time for this network.

wfVinesRtpRtGateNetid.name: wfVinesRtpRtGateNetid
wfVinesRtpRtGateNetid.description: The network ID of the gateway to this network.

wfVinesRtpRtGateSvrName.name: wfVinesRtpRtGateSvrName
wfVinesRtpRtGateSvrName.description: The name of the gateway server.

wfVinesRtpRtIfType.name: wfVinesRtpRtIfType
wfVinesRtpRtIfType.description: This describes the type of interface.

wfVinesRtpRtType.name: wfVinesRtpRtType
wfVinesRtpRtType.description: This indicates the whether this is a VINES 5.50 router or a VINES 4.11 Router/Server. If learnt as part of a 4.11 RTP or thro' a sequenced RTP or by looking at the network flag in the tuple of a sequenced update

wfVinesRtpRtSeqNumber.name: wfVinesRtpRtSeqNumber
wfVinesRtpRtSeqNumber.description: This attribute will always have a value of 0x0

wfVinesRtpRtTimeStamp.name: wfVinesRtpRtTimeStamp
wfVinesRtpRtTimeStamp.description: This attribute will always have a value of 0x0

wfVinesRtpRtNumPaths.name: wfVinesRtpRtNumPaths
wfVinesRtpRtNumPaths.description: The number of paths to the Network

wfVinesIfNumber.name: wfVinesIfNumber
wfVinesIfNumber.description: This is the number of entries in the Interfaces Table.

wfVinesIfTable.name: wfVinesIfTable
wfVinesIfTable.description: This is the Table of Interfaces.

wfVinesIfEntry.name: wfVinesIfEntry
wfVinesIfEntry.description: An entry to the Interface Table.

wfVinesIfDelete.name: wfVinesIfDelete
wfVinesIfDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Users perform an SNMP set command to create/delete a VINES interface.

wfVinesIfDisable.name: wfVinesIfDisable
wfVinesIfDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Users perform an SNMP set command to enable/disable a VINES interface.

wfVinesIfState.name: wfVinesIfState
wfVinesIfState.description: This parameter reflects the current state of the VINES interface.

wfVinesIfSlot.name: wfVinesIfSlot
wfVinesIfSlot.description: The slot on which this interface is configured.

wfVinesIfLine.name: wfVinesIfLine
wfVinesIfLine.description: The line on which this interface is configured.

wfVinesIfCct.name: wfVinesIfCct
wfVinesIfCct.description: The circuit number for this interface.

wfVinesIfSession.name: wfVinesIfSession
wfVinesIfSession.description: The session number for this interface.

wfVinesIfType.name: wfVinesIfType
wfVinesIfType.description: The type of interface this is.

wfVinesIfAdr.name: wfVinesIfAdr
wfVinesIfAdr.description: The MAC address of this interface.

wfVinesIfDodIpDisable.name: wfVinesIfDodIpDisable
wfVinesIfDodIpDisable.description: This parameter indicates if this interface is enabled to encapsulate VINES packets over DoD IP.

wfVinesIfArpDisable.name: wfVinesIfArpDisable
wfVinesIfArpDisable.description: This parameter indicates if this interface is enabled to support VINES ARP.

wfVinesIfTrEndStation.name: wfVinesIfTrEndStation
wfVinesIfTrEndStation.description: This parameter indicates if this interface is enabled for source routing end station support.

wfVinesIfInPkts.name: wfVinesIfInPkts
wfVinesIfInPkts.description: The number of packets received on this interface.

wfVinesIfInErrs.name: wfVinesIfInErrs
wfVinesIfInErrs.description: The number of packets received with errors.

wfVinesIfOutPkts.name: wfVinesIfOutPkts
wfVinesIfOutPkts.description: The number of packets transmitted on this interface.

wfVinesIfOutErrs.name: wfVinesIfOutErrs
wfVinesIfOutErrs.description: The number of errors on packets transmitted.

wfVinesIfInMsgs.name: wfVinesIfInMsgs
wfVinesIfInMsgs.description: The number of messages received on this interface.

wfVinesIfMux.name: wfVinesIfMux
wfVinesIfMux.description: Muxing scheme for this interface. VINES currently only supports Ethernet encapsulation, but they plan to switch to SNAP.

wfVinesIfFwdDrops.name: wfVinesIfFwdDrops
wfVinesIfFwdDrops.description: The number of pakets that were dropped because of no forwarding information for the destination.

wfVinesIfZeroHopDrops.name: wfVinesIfZeroHopDrops
wfVinesIfZeroHopDrops.description: The number of pakets that were dropped because of a zero hop count.

wfVinesIfIcpInErrorNotifs.name: wfVinesIfIcpInErrorNotifs
wfVinesIfIcpInErrorNotifs.description: The number of ICP error notification packets received.

wfVinesIfIcpInMetricNotifs.name: wfVinesIfIcpInMetricNotifs
wfVinesIfIcpInMetricNotifs.description: The number of ICP metric notification packets received.

wfVinesIfIcpInErrors.name: wfVinesIfIcpInErrors
wfVinesIfIcpInErrors.description: The number of ICP packets received with errors.

wfVinesIfIcpOutErrorNotifs.name: wfVinesIfIcpOutErrorNotifs
wfVinesIfIcpOutErrorNotifs.description: The number of ICP error notification packets transmitted.

wfVinesIfIcpOutMetricNotifs.name: wfVinesIfIcpOutMetricNotifs
wfVinesIfIcpOutMetricNotifs.description: The number of ICP metric notification packets transmitted.

wfVinesIfArpInQueries.name: wfVinesIfArpInQueries
wfVinesIfArpInQueries.description: The number of ARP queries received.

wfVinesIfArpInAssgReqs.name: wfVinesIfArpInAssgReqs
wfVinesIfArpInAssgReqs.description: The number of ARP assignment requests received.

wfVinesIfArpInErrors.name: wfVinesIfArpInErrors
wfVinesIfArpInErrors.description: The number of ARP packets received with errors.

wfVinesIfArpOutServRsps.name: wfVinesIfArpOutServRsps
wfVinesIfArpOutServRsps.description: The number of ARP service responses sent.

wfVinesIfArpOutAssgRsps.name: wfVinesIfArpOutAssgRsps
wfVinesIfArpOutAssgRsps.description: The number of ARP assignment responses sent.

wfVinesIfInRedirects.name: wfVinesIfInRedirects
wfVinesIfInRedirects.description: The number of Redirect packets received.

wfVinesIfOutRedirects.name: wfVinesIfOutRedirects
wfVinesIfOutRedirects.description: The number of Redirect packets sent.

wfVinesIfEchoInPkts.name: wfVinesIfEchoInPkts
wfVinesIfEchoInPkts.description: The number of Echo packets received.

wfVinesIfEchoOutPkts.name: wfVinesIfEchoOutPkts
wfVinesIfEchoOutPkts.description: The number of Echo packets sent.

wfVinesIfReassFails.name: wfVinesIfReassFails
wfVinesIfReassFails.description: The number of packet reassemblies that failed.

wfVinesIfRemClientPrivDisable.name: wfVinesIfRemClientPrivDisable
wfVinesIfRemClientPrivDisable.description: This parameter indicates that this interface will allow remote clients privileges on this segment. This means that a client is not restricted to being within one hop of a VINES server.

wfVinesIfCost.name: wfVinesIfCost
wfVinesIfCost.description: The Interface Cost The default is null - meaning use the Banyan specified cost. Otherwise, the configured value wfVinesIfCfgCost will be used.

wfVinesIfSyncPortNumber.name: wfVinesIfSyncPortNumber
wfVinesIfSyncPortNumber.description: The Sync port number required to determine number of RTP packets sent for each network. It can only take a value between 1 - 4. It correspond to the Sync port number on this slot only. If it is 4.2 for example, then the port number should be 2.

wfVinesIfInLackRescError.name: wfVinesIfInLackRescError
wfVinesIfInLackRescError.description: Failed to duplicate packet due to lack of resource.

wfVinesIfOutLackRescError.name: wfVinesIfOutLackRescError
wfVinesIfOutLackRescError.description: Failed to duplicate packet due to lack of resource.

wfVinesIfRtpRecv.name: wfVinesIfRtpRecv
wfVinesIfRtpRecv.description: The number of RTP packets received.

wfVinesIfRtpSent.name: wfVinesIfRtpSent
wfVinesIfRtpSent.description: The number of RTP packets sent.

wfVinesIfCfgAdr.name: wfVinesIfCfgAdr
wfVinesIfCfgAdr.description: The configured MAC address of this interface.

wfVinesIfNumRoutes.name: wfVinesIfNumRoutes
wfVinesIfNumRoutes.description: Number of routes cached in the forwarding table

wfVinesIfCostUsed.name: wfVinesIfCostUsed
wfVinesIfCostUsed.description: The Interface Cost used by the router

wfVinesIfFrpEnable.name: wfVinesIfFrpEnable
wfVinesIfFrpEnable.description: Parameter to indicate whether this interface is to support the use of FRP header

wfVinesIfSeqArpInQueries.name: wfVinesIfSeqArpInQueries
wfVinesIfSeqArpInQueries.description: The number of Sequenced ARP queries received.

wfVinesIfSeqArpInAssgReqs.name: wfVinesIfSeqArpInAssgReqs
wfVinesIfSeqArpInAssgReqs.description: The number of Sequenced ARP assignment requests received.

wfVinesIfSeqArpInErrors.name: wfVinesIfSeqArpInErrors
wfVinesIfSeqArpInErrors.description: The number of Sequenced ARP packets received with errors.

wfVinesIfSeqArpOutServRsps.name: wfVinesIfSeqArpOutServRsps
wfVinesIfSeqArpOutServRsps.description: The number of Sequenced ARP service responses sent.

wfVinesIfSeqArpOutAssgRsps.name: wfVinesIfSeqArpOutAssgRsps
wfVinesIfSeqArpOutAssgRsps.description: The number of Sequenced ARP assignment responses sent.

wfVinesIfInSeqRedirects.name: wfVinesIfInSeqRedirects
wfVinesIfInSeqRedirects.description: The number of Sequenced Redirect packets received.

wfVinesIfOutSeqRedirects.name: wfVinesIfOutSeqRedirects
wfVinesIfOutSeqRedirects.description: The number of Sequenced Redirect packets sent.

wfVinesIfSeqRtpRecv.name: wfVinesIfSeqRtpRecv
wfVinesIfSeqRtpRecv.description: The number of RTP packets received.

wfVinesIfSeqRtpSent.name: wfVinesIfSeqRtpSent
wfVinesIfSeqRtpSent.description: The number of RTP packets sent.

wfVinesIfRtpGenerationDisable.name: wfVinesIfRtpGenerationDisable
wfVinesIfRtpGenerationDisable.description: This parameter will be used to disable the RTP generation on an interface, where static routes may be configured

wfVinesIfInverseArpEnable.name: wfVinesIfInverseArpEnable
wfVinesIfInverseArpEnable.description: This is to enable the use of Inverse ARP protocol to learn nbrs in a Frame Relay/ATM network when a new dlci comes up

wfVinesIfSTalkSplitHorizon.name: wfVinesIfSTalkSplitHorizon
wfVinesIfSTalkSplitHorizon.description: This is to disable the use of split horizon for STALK packets so as to support a partially meshed Frame Relay Network for VINES

wfVinesIfPermWanNbr.name: wfVinesIfPermWanNbr
wfVinesIfPermWanNbr.description: This is to enable the use of Permanent Non sequenced Nbrs for Non sequenced neighbors over a WAN link, so that these are not aged every 1 hour, when using Automode/Sequenced Mode.

wfVinesIfNumFwdEntries.name: wfVinesIfNumFwdEntries
wfVinesIfNumFwdEntries.description: This counts the number of forwarding entries on this interface

wfVinesIfNumNonSeqNbrs.name: wfVinesIfNumNonSeqNbrs
wfVinesIfNumNonSeqNbrs.description: This counts the number of Non sequenced Nbrs

wfVinesIfNumSeqNbrs.name: wfVinesIfNumSeqNbrs
wfVinesIfNumSeqNbrs.description: This counts the number of sequenced Nbrs

wfVinesIfRedirectEnable.name: wfVinesIfRedirectEnable
wfVinesIfRedirectEnable.description: Parameter to indicate whether this interface is to generate RTP redirect packets

wfVinesIfX25VCNumber.name: wfVinesIfX25VCNumber
wfVinesIfX25VCNumber.description: This is the number of entries in the X.25 Virtual Circuit Table.

wfVinesIfX25VCTable.name: wfVinesIfX25VCTable
wfVinesIfX25VCTable.description: This is the Table of X.25 Virtual Circuits.

wfVinesIfX25VCEntry.name: wfVinesIfX25VCEntry
wfVinesIfX25VCEntry.description: An entry in the Table of X.25 Virtual Circuits.

wfVinesIfX25VCSlot.name: wfVinesIfX25VCSlot
wfVinesIfX25VCSlot.description: The number of the slot in which the card is installed.

wfVinesIfX25VCLine.name: wfVinesIfX25VCLine
wfVinesIfX25VCLine.description: For a serial line, this is the number of the line on the card.

wfVinesIfX25VCCct.name: wfVinesIfX25VCCct
wfVinesIfX25VCCct.description: Local circuit number for this Virtual Circuit.

wfVinesIfX25VCSession.name: wfVinesIfX25VCSession
wfVinesIfX25VCSession.description: Local session number for this Virtual Circuit.

wfVinesIfX25VCTotIn.name: wfVinesIfX25VCTotIn
wfVinesIfX25VCTotIn.description: The total number of VINES IP packets received on this VC. Depending on the size of the X.25 packets received, more than one X.25 packet can make up a VINES IP packet.

wfVinesIfX25VCTotOut.name: wfVinesIfX25VCTotOut
wfVinesIfX25VCTotOut.description: The total number of VINES IP packets sent on this VC. Depending on the size of the X.25 packets sent, more than one X.25 packet can make up a VINES IP packet.

wfVinesIfX25VCInErrs.name: wfVinesIfX25VCInErrs
wfVinesIfX25VCInErrs.description: The total number of input errors.

wfVinesIfX25VCOutErrs.name: wfVinesIfX25VCOutErrs
wfVinesIfX25VCOutErrs.description: The total number of output errors.

wfVinesIfX25VCPktsOut.name: wfVinesIfX25VCPktsOut
wfVinesIfX25VCPktsOut.description: The total number of X.25 packets transmitted on this VC.

wfVinesIfX25VCPktsAwaitAck.name: wfVinesIfX25VCPktsAwaitAck
wfVinesIfX25VCPktsAwaitAck.description: Total number of X.25 packets transmitted on this VC waiting for ACK.

wfVinesIfX25VCBytesOut.name: wfVinesIfX25VCBytesOut
wfVinesIfX25VCBytesOut.description: Total Bytes transmitted on this VC.

wfVinesIfX25VCBytesAwaitAck.name: wfVinesIfX25VCBytesAwaitAck
wfVinesIfX25VCBytesAwaitAck.description: Total bytes transmitted on this VC that are waiting for ACK.

wfVinesIfX25VCPktsIn.name: wfVinesIfX25VCPktsIn
wfVinesIfX25VCPktsIn.description: Total X.25 packets received on this VC.

wfVinesIfX25VCBytesIn.name: wfVinesIfX25VCBytesIn
wfVinesIfX25VCBytesIn.description: Total Bytes received on this VC.

wfVinesIfX25VCResetsIn.name: wfVinesIfX25VCResetsIn
wfVinesIfX25VCResetsIn.description: Number of X.25 reset packets received on this VC.

wfVinesIfX25VCResetsOut.name: wfVinesIfX25VCResetsOut
wfVinesIfX25VCResetsOut.description: Number of X.25 reset packets transmitted on this VC.

wfVinesTrafficFilterCreate.name: wfVinesTrafficFilterCreate
wfVinesTrafficFilterCreate.description: Defines the existence of the traffic filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfVinesTrafficFilterEnable.name: wfVinesTrafficFilterEnable
wfVinesTrafficFilterEnable.description: Defines whether or not the traffic filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfVinesTrafficFilterStatus.name: wfVinesTrafficFilterStatus
wfVinesTrafficFilterStatus.description: Defines the current status of the traffic filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfVinesTrafficFilterCounter.name: wfVinesTrafficFilterCounter
wfVinesTrafficFilterCounter.description: The number of received packets that have matched this rule.

wfVinesTrafficFilterCircuit.name: wfVinesTrafficFilterCircuit
wfVinesTrafficFilterCircuit.description: The ID of the Circuit to which the filter is applied.

wfVinesNameTable.name: wfVinesNameTable
wfVinesNameTable.description: This is the Name-to-Address Binding Table.

wfVinesNameEntry.name: wfVinesNameEntry
wfVinesNameEntry.description: An entry in the Table of Names.

wfVinesNameDelete.name: wfVinesNameDelete
wfVinesNameDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Users perform an SNMP set command to create/delete this name.

wfVinesNameDisable.name: wfVinesNameDisable
wfVinesNameDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Users perform an SNMP set command to enable/disable a name.

wfVinesNameNetid.name: wfVinesNameNetid
wfVinesNameNetid.description: This is the network number for the host.

wfVinesNameHost.name: wfVinesNameHost
wfVinesNameHost.description: This is the name of the host.

wfVinesNameSubNetid.name: wfVinesNameSubNetid
wfVinesNameSubNetid.description: This is the subnetwork number for the host.

wfVinesArpDelete.name: wfVinesArpDelete
wfVinesArpDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object in order to create/delete ARP.

wfVinesArpDisable.name: wfVinesArpDisable
wfVinesArpDisable.description: Enable/Disable Parameter indicates whether this ARP record is enabled or disabled.

wfVinesArpSubnetid.name: wfVinesArpSubnetid
wfVinesArpSubnetid.description: The next subnetwork ID to be assigned.

wfVinesArpSubnetBlock.name: wfVinesArpSubnetBlock
wfVinesArpSubnetBlock.description: The size of the block of subnet ids a slot can grab.

wfVinesArpAssignDeniedPkts.name: wfVinesArpAssignDeniedPkts
wfVinesArpAssignDeniedPkts.description: Number of ARP Assignment packets received for which we didn't have a free subnet number.

wfVinesSeqRtpNbrNumber.name: wfVinesSeqRtpNbrNumber
wfVinesSeqRtpNbrNumber.description: Number of entries in the Table of 5.5 Neighbors.

wfVinesAggrInPkts.name: wfVinesAggrInPkts
wfVinesAggrInPkts.description: The total number of packets received

wfVinesAggrOutPkts.name: wfVinesAggrOutPkts
wfVinesAggrOutPkts.description: The total number of datagrams sent (includes datagrams forwarded)

wfVinesAggrFwdPkts.name: wfVinesAggrFwdPkts
wfVinesAggrFwdPkts.description: The total number of datagrams forwarded

wfVinesAggrInXsumErrs.name: wfVinesAggrInXsumErrs
wfVinesAggrInXsumErrs.description: The total number of datagrams destined for a local entity that were dropped because of a checksum error.

wfVinesAggrBcastPkts.name: wfVinesAggrBcastPkts
wfVinesAggrBcastPkts.description: The total number of broadcast packets sent (includes locally generated broadcasts).

wfVinesAggrOutNoRoutes.name: wfVinesAggrOutNoRoutes
wfVinesAggrOutNoRoutes.description: The total number of packets queued for transmission thet were discarded because the destination was unreachable.

wfVinesAggrInHopCountErrs.name: wfVinesAggrInHopCountErrs
wfVinesAggrInHopCountErrs.description: The total number of pakets that were dropped because of a zero hop count.

wfVinesAggrInIcpErrs.name: wfVinesAggrInIcpErrs
wfVinesAggrInIcpErrs.description: The total number of ICP error notification packets received.

wfVinesAggrInIcpMetrics.name: wfVinesAggrInIcpMetrics
wfVinesAggrInIcpMetrics.description: The total number of ICP metric notification packets received.

wfVinesAggrOutIcpErrs.name: wfVinesAggrOutIcpErrs
wfVinesAggrOutIcpErrs.description: The total number of ICP error notification packets transmitted.

wfVinesAggrOutIcpMetrics.name: wfVinesAggrOutIcpMetrics
wfVinesAggrOutIcpMetrics.description: The total number of ICP metric notification packets transmitted.

wfVinesAggrInArpQueries.name: wfVinesAggrInArpQueries
wfVinesAggrInArpQueries.description: The total number of ARP queries received.

wfVinesAggrInArpAssigns.name: wfVinesAggrInArpAssigns
wfVinesAggrInArpAssigns.description: The total number of ARP assignment requests received.
